                <note rend="inline" type="source">893.102H/325: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Reinsch</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-06-09T21:00:00+08:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 9, 1919—9 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 9—5:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Your [<hi rend="italic">my</hi>] October 1st, 1917. Decision in this matter is
                    urgent as [activity] of American firm greatly prejudiced by failure to <pb
                        facs="0887" n="789" xml:id="pg_789"/> [acquire] land in Harbin. I beg to
                    request authorization to agree to Anglo-Russian agreement with view safeguarding
                    of [interests].</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Reinsch</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
